<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900725-0110</DOCNO><DOCID>900725-0110.</DOCID><HL>   Niagara Exchange Halts Pact</HL><DATE>07/25/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   NIEX BKLY</CO><LP>   BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Niagara Exchange Corp. said it hasrescinded an agreement under which W.R. Berkley Corp.,Greenwich, Conn., had purchased 970,000 shares of Niagarapreferred stock for $8.2 million.   The agreement was disallowed by the New York Department ofInsurance. Niagara sought the investment to replace fundspaid out last year by a Niagara subsidiary on claims arisingfrom Hurricane Hugo.</LP><TEXT>   Niagara and W.R. Berkley are both property and casualtyinsurance holding companies. The companies said they arecontinuing to discuss a possible investment in Niagara byBerkley.</TEXT></DOC>